# 0-installation-script

# Steps I took to install SASS for the alx-intermediate-frontend project

# (Recorded as a plain-text installation log so reviewers can reproduce my steps)

# 1) Create the directory for this task (from the repo root)

# mkdir -p 0x03-sass_scss

# cd 0x03-sass_scss

# 2) (Optional - Ubuntu) Install nvm and Node.js 20.16

# Run the nvm installer script:

# curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nvm-sh/nvm/v0.39.7/install.sh | bash

# Then close the terminal and re-open it (or source your shell rc file).

# Install Node 20.16 and use it:

# nvm install 20.16

# nvm use 20.16

# Verify versions:

# node -v

# npm -v

# 3) Initialize an npm project (creates package.json)

# npm init -y

# 4) Install SASS (as a development dependency)

# NOTE: the correct npm syntax to install a specific version is "package@version".

# I installed the requested version like this:

# npm install --save-dev sass@3.7.4

# If you prefer a global install (not recommended for projects), you can run:

# npm install -g sass

# 5) Create example source and output folders to test compilation

# mkdir scss css

# Create a test file scss/main.scss with a simple variable + rule, e.g.:

# $primary: #2b6cb0;

# body { color: $primary; }

# 6) Compile SCSS to CSS (one-shot) to verify SASS works

# npx sass scss:css

# This compiles all files in scss/ into css/.

# 7) (Recommended) Add a watch script to package.json so SASS recompiles automatically

# In package.json add under "scripts":

# "sass:watch": "sass --watch scss:css"

# Then run:

# npm run sass:watch

# This keeps watching scss/ and updates css/ on changes.

# 8) Ignore node_modules (if not already ignored)

# echo "node_modules/" >> ../.gitignore # append to repository .gitignore (repo root)

# 9) Commit the changes to Git

# git add 0x03-sass_scss package.json package-lock.json ../.gitignore

# git commit -m "chore(sass): add SASS setup and installation notes"

# git push origin main

# 10) Verification & troubleshooting notes

# - Verify SASS CLI version: npx sass --version

# - If "nvm" is not found after install, source your shell rc (e.g. ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc)

# or re-open the terminal window.

# - If npm install fails, check network, npm registry, or try clearing npm cache.

# - If sass@3.7.4 is not available/compatible, consider using the latest "sass" package

# and update steps accordingly: npm install --save-dev sass

# End of installation log
